I’m super excited to announce the launch of my non-profit @thepeaceprojectla 🕊️: empowering girls around the world and providing access to the peace of mind they deserve 🤍
Last year I went on a trip to Ghana, Africa to visit The Cape Coast school for Deaf & Blind @memphis.foundation on a search for something deeper. 
 Overwhelmed by the love and connection I made with the girls at the school I made a promise to myself . Though it is unfamiliar territory, it’s been amazing to see how doors have opened after commiting my mind and spirit to this mission. It’s amazing to see the world align when you choose to follow your destiny. 
  A special shout out to some of the incredible women who have guided me in getting this project off the ground @khloekares & @tina_wright 
 Period Poverty is big problem young woman are facing. Lack of menstrual care forces girls to miss school leading millions to drop out every year. 

The Peace Projects first initiative is to provide a years supply of sanitary pads to the 200 girls at the Cape Coast school . To find out how to be apart of the solution visit projectpeacela.com🤍
